node.title: Four-year-old girl, two teenagers test positive to COVID-19, the NT's three new local cases
node.alt: The quiet main street of Katherine during a COVID-19 lockdown.
node.description: The Northern Territory has recorded three more local COVID cases overnight, taking its latest outbreak total to 71.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded three\u00a0new local cases of COVID-19 in the past 24 hours, including in a four-year-old girl.", "NT Health Minister Natasha Fyles today said all of the cases had been recorded in the town of Katherine, where the Territory's local outbreak began more than a month ago.", "A four-year-old girl from\u00a0the Katherine East area, who is a family contact of a case detected last week, is one of the people who has tested positive.", "Ms Fyles said the girl\u00a0has\u00a0been in the\u00a0Howard Springs quarantine facility throughout her infectious period.\u00a0", "Two Katherine East girls, aged 15 and 17, have also tested positive.", "More to come."]
